# YARD documentation

All methods — public and private — must have YARD docs with `@param`,
`@return`, and `@raise` tags where applicable.

```ruby
# GOOD
# Resolve a git ref to a full 40-char SHA.
#
# @param repo [String] git remote URL
# @param ref  [String] tag name, branch name, or commit SHA
# @return [String] full 40-char SHA
# @raise [RefResolutionError] if no match found
def resolve_ref(repo, ref)
```

Comments must only describe what this code does, not what other layers do.
Do not mention concerns the layer doesn't own (see separation-of-concerns rule).
